\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 cups low-sodium chicken broth\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 teaspoons kosher salt, plus extra for seasoning\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/4 cups polenta or yellow cornmeal\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup freshly grated Parmesan\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup whole milk, at room temperature\
{\listtext	\'95	}5 tablespoons unsalted butter, at room temperature, cut into 1/2-inch pieces\
{\listtext	\'95	}Freshly ground black pepper\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Bring the broth, 2 1/2 cups water and the salt to a boil in a heavy 5-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Gradually whisk in the polenta. Reduce the heat to low and cook, stirring often, until the mixture thickens and the cornmeal is tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat. Add the Parmesan, milk and butter. Stir until the butter and Parmesan have melted. Season with salt and pepper.\
